  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Frame agreement with NGO (SASK)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is a project for four existing PSI (Public Services International) affiliates and one potential affiliate in Indonesia. It follows from the ratification of ILO Conventions 87 and 98 which made it possible for state owned enterprise unions to leave KORPRI (Indonesian Civil Servants Corps), the state controlled umbrella organisation for the public sector and to establish &apos;reformasi&apos; unions. The project strategy allows each of the unions to prioritise their own issues as well as to participate in joint skills workshops. Following training the unions will conduct in stages over three years campaigns on energy privatisation, dues collection, recruitment, financial management, gender equality and membership awareness.</narrative>
  </description>
